instruction:
An IIFE (Immediately Invoked Function Expression) runs the moment it's defined:

```js
(function() {
  // runs immediately
})();
```

Useful for: running setup code without polluting the global scope, creating private variables.

Run this and see how IIFE creates a private scope.

starter:
const result = (function() {
  const secret = "hidden inside IIFE";
  const computed = 6 * 7;
  return { computed, message: "IIFE ran!" };
})();

console.log(result.computed);
console.log(result.message);
try {
  console.log(secret); // can't access this
} catch(e) {
  console.log("secret is not accessible outside IIFE");
}
